<subSubSection id="56AC63C9FFA6FFDED0F32697FB0221D8" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1E093042FFA6FFDED0F32697FB0221D8" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED0F32697FED522DB" bold="true" box="[199,328,476,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">Comments</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="D9B64BC1FFA6FFDED1682697FD3122DA" authority="Boldrini, 2017" authorityName="Boldrini" authorityYear="2017" box="[348,684,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavieri" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED1682697FE5522DA" box="[348,456,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">Miroculis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED1E92697FDD422DA" box="[477,585,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">Miroculis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED26A2696FD3122DA" box="[606,684,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">xavieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="37F1512BFFA6FFDED28C2697FC8B22DB" box="[696,790,476,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" rank="species">
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED28C2697FC8B22DB" bold="true" box="[696,790,476,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares some characteristics with 
<taxonomicName id="D9B64BC1FFA6FFDED4912697FE2D2136" authority="Savage, 1987" authorityName="Savage" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosus" subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED4912697FA8C22DA" box="[1189,1297,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">Miroculis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED5132697FA0E22DA" box="[1319,1427,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">Miroculis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED0A3254BFE9A2136" box="[151,263,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">nebulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7A274DB3FFA6FFDED127254BFE2D2136" author="Savage" box="[275,432,512,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" refString="Savage, H. M. (1987) Two new SpecieS of Miroculis from Cerro de la Neblina, Venezuela with new diStribution recordS for Miroculis fittkaui and Microphlebia surinamensis (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae). Aquatic Insects, 9, 97 - 108. httpS: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01650428709361279" type="journal article" year="1987">Savage, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
such as, compound eye with a short stalk (length 0.5 x width), forewing with MP2 connected to MP1 by a cross vein and IMP free basally; and hind wing brown apically (
<figureCitation id="868D2CC7FFA6FFDED45E256DFB202111" box="[1130,1213,550,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[366,1226,555,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[340,1247,540,1935]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Male imago of Miroculis (Miroculis) xavieri sp. nov.: 11) lateral view, habituS; 12) forewing; 13) hind wing; 14) genitalia; 15) apex of peniS, detail." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892959/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="D9B64BC1FFA6FFDED5712563FF78214B" authority="Boldrini, 2017" authorityName="Boldrini" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavieri" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED5712563FAF92111" box="[1349,1380,552,575]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED5402563FA0E2111" box="[1396,1427,552,575]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED0A32505FF78214B" box="[151,229,590,613]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">xavieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="37F1512BFFA6FFDED0DF2506FED92148" box="[235,324,589,614]" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" rank="species">
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED0DF2506FED92148" bold="true" box="[235,324,589,614]" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="D9B64BC1FFA6FFDED1E32505FD3E214B" authorityName="Savage" authorityYear="1987" box="[471,675,589,614]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosus" subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED1E32505FE68214B" box="[471,501,590,613]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED2312505FDB9214B" box="[517,548,590,613]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED2072506FD3E214B" box="[563,675,589,613]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">nebulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a hyaline forewing with crossveins tinged brown, base of forceps segment I with basal third portion narrowing gradually toward apex and washed with dark gray on apical third, and penis as long as forceps segment I. Otherwise, 
<taxonomicName id="D9B64BC1FFA6FFDED31125DDFC682183" authorityName="Savage" authorityYear="1987" box="[805,1013,661,686]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosus" subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED31125DDFCD92183" box="[805,836,662,685]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED36125DDFCE92183" box="[853,884,662,685]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="2CC2EC50FFA6FFDED3B125DEFC682183" box="[901,1013,661,685]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">nebulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the forewing completely washed with brown and with few hyaline areas, forceps segment I with basal third narrowing abruptly toward apex and equally pigmented as in the other segments, and penis longer than segment forceps I (1.5 x).
</paragraph>
